@MarcoFalke recently made a PR to to make the logo black: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/16571

In addition to avoiding bike-shedding, one objection was that we use different colors for the different networks (mainnet orange, testnet green, regtest, signet, etc). However that distinction could be achieved in other ways, and is mostly relevant for developers.

Apologies for the blasphemy but I can hardly see the difference between those two fonts, so if it keeps lawyers away, I'm fine with switching.
